system to the document.

00:15:51.390 --> 00:15:54.690
Today in Mac OS 9,
if I want to save a document

00:15:54.780 --> 00:15:58.170
in my word processor,
I'm presented with what's called

00:15:58.250 --> 00:16:00.500
an application modal dialog.

00:16:00.500 --> 00:16:05.220
There's nothing else I can do in that
application while that dialog is open.

00:16:06.070 --> 00:16:10.080
I can switch to another application,
but maybe that's not what I want.

00:16:10.180 --> 00:16:13.230
Maybe I want to switch to another
document to check something.

00:16:13.530 --> 00:16:16.500
So now we've taken modality
to the document level.

00:16:16.530 --> 00:16:23.950
Each document-- I can open a save sheet
on five separate documents if I choose.

00:16:25.280 --> 00:16:29.770
Now the interesting thing about
sheets to reinforce this document

00:16:29.800 --> 00:16:33.250
modality is that sheets are attached
to the document that they were

00:16:33.320 --> 00:16:35.380
generated from or that they apply to.

00:16:35.380 --> 00:16:38.400
So as I move the document around,
the sheet follows it.

00:16:40.490 --> 00:16:44.920
That's an example of how a behavior
reinforces this relationship

00:16:45.030 --> 00:16:46.900
between these two windows.

