00:36:26.660 --> 00:36:28.790
So first of all, we wanted to make things
a little bit bigger.

00:36:28.800 --> 00:36:34.270
We had the opportunity to
think about how elements could

00:36:34.450 --> 00:36:37.060
should scale in Aqua and
how they could be larger.

00:36:37.060 --> 00:36:40.990
So we decided to break out of the
boundary of small 32 by 32 icons,

00:36:41.090 --> 00:36:42.370
go a little bit larger.

00:36:42.450 --> 00:36:45.020
But rather than take a
small incremental step,

00:36:45.020 --> 00:36:45.020
we

00:36:45.100 --> 00:36:46.600
We decided to take a big one.

00:36:46.600 --> 00:36:49.700
In part because the doc uses
it when it's magnifying items.

00:36:52.400 --> 00:36:55.170
But what's more interesting
about this icon is because of

00:36:55.180 --> 00:36:59.880
the limitations at the time,
it was, in essence, iconic.

00:36:59.890 --> 00:37:02.600
It couldn't communicate very much.

00:37:03.100 --> 00:37:05.040
The hand,
now I can make out that there's a hand

00:37:05.040 --> 00:37:09.290
here and I think it's holding what
looks to be maybe a pen or a pencil.

00:37:09.290 --> 00:37:12.980
I believe this was the icon
for MacWrite originally.

00:37:14.400 --> 00:37:17.670
And it just is trying to
capture what this tool does,

00:37:17.670 --> 00:37:21.590
but it doesn't really communicate what
you might accomplish by using this tool.

00:37:21.600 --> 00:37:27.990
It doesn't have any
emotional qualities to it.

00:37:30.980 --> 00:37:35.600
So what we wanted to achieve with
Aqua was with our icon style.

00:37:35.620 --> 00:37:38.560
Because we had the opportunity to
put such tremendous detail into

00:37:38.630 --> 00:37:42.750
our icons because they were larger,
is we wanted to move towards

00:37:42.790 --> 00:37:44.040
a more emotive style.

00:37:45.570 --> 00:37:51.740
We wanted an application icon to say,
I'm not just a word processor,

00:37:51.740 --> 00:37:52.820
but here's the things I can do.

00:37:52.820 --> 00:37:54.430
I can create letters for you.

00:37:54.560 --> 00:37:57.060
We can create letters.

00:37:57.100 --> 00:38:02.010
In this case, this example is our preview
application for looking at images.

00:38:04.620 --> 00:38:09.100
And it kind of suggests the kind
of reward or emotional reward you

00:38:09.100 --> 00:38:11.800
might get by using this application
to look at your photographs

00:38:12.290 --> 00:38:14.160
or other people's photographs.

00:38:15.180 --> 00:38:18.200
But we think this is a subtle
while very important shift in how

00:38:18.200 --> 00:38:21.050
we're approaching our icon designs.

00:38:22.190 --> 00:38:27.870
The other thing we did is we've actually
designed what we're calling genres.

00:38:27.960 --> 00:38:33.170
Now we've always had icon families
and families describe either icons

00:38:33.280 --> 00:38:38.340
Icons belonging to an application,
for example, the application icon and

00:38:38.350 --> 00:38:38.630
its corresponding document.

00:38:39.750 --> 00:38:41.760
or an extension or a control panel.

00:38:41.760 --> 00:38:45.580
We've always described those as families.

00:38:45.580 --> 00:38:48.770
Now in the case of multiple applications,
we can of course have different

00:38:48.770 --> 00:38:50.040
kinds of applications.

00:38:50.060 --> 00:38:52.890
We can have applications which
the user may use to author

00:38:52.890 --> 00:38:56.770
something or produce something,
perhaps a letter or a website.

00:38:56.950 --> 00:39:00.760
But we also have utilities,
applications in which are

00:39:00.760 --> 00:39:03.690
of a more technical nature,
applications that perhaps are best left

00:39:03.690 --> 00:39:06.250
to somebody who knows what they're doing.

00:39:07.360 --> 00:39:09.650
So we've described what
we're calling genres.

00:39:09.660 --> 00:39:12.370
And I'll show you two examples,
two different collections

00:39:12.370 --> 00:39:14.000
of each of those.

00:39:14.140 --> 00:39:16.060
As I mentioned, the large size.

00:39:16.110 --> 00:39:19.030
Rather than taking a small
increment going 48 by 48,

00:39:19.110 --> 00:39:21.630
64 by 64,
we just went all the way up to 128.

00:39:21.690 --> 00:39:24.900
I don't think we'll have to
revisit this size for a while.

00:39:24.920 --> 00:39:27.480
I think if you do an icon now,
the larger size,

00:39:27.520 --> 00:39:29.500
I think we're safe for a while.

00:39:30.130 --> 00:39:33.530
Now what we've also done,
we haven't changed the format by which we

00:39:34.030 --> 00:39:35.580
preserve or save our icons in our apps.

00:39:35.700 --> 00:39:38.040
We're still using the ICNS format
introduced in Mac OS 9.

00:39:38.040 --> 00:39:42.160
So we can support what we're
calling hints at smaller sizes.

00:39:42.170 --> 00:39:46.730
Now while you can take 128 by 128 icons,
scale it down quite nicely,

00:39:46.740 --> 00:39:51.460
and it preserves its image quite well,
right down to as small as 48 by 48.

00:39:51.460 --> 00:39:55.350
Once you get down to about 32 by 32,
or especially down to 16 by 16,

00:39:55.540 --> 00:39:57.550
those scaled icons start
to lose their meaning.

00:39:57.620 --> 00:39:59.340
There's too much information.

00:40:00.000 --> 00:40:03.560
So hints allow you to design
simpler icons at those sizes.

00:40:03.620 --> 00:40:07.040
And as you scale them down,
the system will swap in these

00:40:07.470 --> 00:40:11.080
hints and therefore present a
simpler icon at the smaller sizes.

00:40:12.310 --> 00:40:13.800
That's an important concept.

00:40:13.840 --> 00:40:15.690
It also allows you to
preserve your existing icons.

00:40:15.720 --> 00:40:19.200
If you decide you're taking your
existing icons forward into Aqua,

00:40:19.200 --> 00:40:23.520
you can save your 16 by 16, 32 by 32s,
you can use those today and

00:40:23.760 --> 00:40:26.140
just create a larger one,
larger 128.

00:40:26.250 --> 00:40:28.040
There you may want to put more detail in.

00:40:29.520 --> 00:40:32.760
So here's an example of
our user application genre.

00:40:32.790 --> 00:40:36.140
These are all applications which
you use to author something,

00:40:36.150 --> 00:40:38.870
or in the case of preview,
just to view something.

00:40:41.300 --> 00:40:45.240
These are intended to not
just say I'm an application,

00:40:45.240 --> 00:40:49.600
